==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[porter]]'', meaning "wear" or "carry", + suffix ''[[-able]]''

===Adjective===
'''portable'''

# Able to be [[carry|carried]] or easily [[move]]d.
# (''computing'') Of [[software]], able to be run on multiple [[hardware]] or [[operating system]]s.

===Noun===
''a'' '''portable''' (''plural'': '''[[portables]]''')

# A portable [[toilet]]; a self-contained [[outhouse]].
# Any [[temporary]] [[building]] that is portable.
# A hand-held electronic device.

====Synonyms====
* (''portable toilet''): [[port-a-john]], [[porta-kybo]], [[portaloo]], [[porta-potty]], [[port-a-san]], [[port-o-let]], [[sani-privy]], [[turdis]]

